  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/pool.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: wave 256 theme — multiprocessing.pool.Pool class method co_varnames for map/apply. NEW in extra126: Pool.map.__code__.co_varnames[0]=='self'; Pool.map.__code__.co_argcount==4 (self, func, iterable, chunksize); Pool.map.__code__.co_varnames[1]=='func'; Pool.map.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==4; Pool.apply.__code__.co_varnames[0]=='self'; Pool.apply.__code__.co_argcount==4 (self, func, args, kwds); Pool.apply.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==4; Pool.imap.__code__.co_varnames[0]=='self'; Pool.imap.__code__.co_argcount==4; Pool.imap.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==6; Pool.starmap.__code__.co_argcount==4; Pool.starmap.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==4; Pool.map_async.__code__.co_argcount==6; Pool.map_async.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==6; Pool.apply_async.__code__.co_argcount==6. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.pool.Pool.map.__code__.co_varnames.__len__() == 4. Pool.map is defined as 'def map(self, func, iterable, chunksize=None)'; co_varnames has exactly 4 entries (self, func, iterable, chunksize) with no additional local variables beyond the 4 positional params. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.pool.Pool.imap.__code__.co_varnames.__len__() == 6. imap is defined as 'def imap(self, func, iterable, chunksize=1)' with 4 positional params plus 2 local variables ('result', 'task_batches'); imap is an iterator version of map that lazily yields results. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.pool.Pool.map_async.__code__.co_argcount == 6. map_async is defined as 'def map_async(self, func, iterable, chunksize=None, callback=None, error_callback=None)' with 6 positional params. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
