invariant multiprocessing_extra126.Pool_starmap_qualname_len_12:
  description: "multiprocessing.pool.Pool.starmap.__qualname__.__len__() == 12 — Pool.starmap.__qualname__ is 'Pool.starmap' (12 chars: 'Pool.'=5 + 'starmap'=7 = 12); this is the longest synchronous-variant method qualname in this spec; compare qualname lengths: map=8, imap=9, apply=10, starmap=12; for the async variants: map_async=14, apply_async=16, starmap_async=18; 'starmap' is 7 chars: 'star'=4+'map'=3=7; starmap applies func to each argument tuple in iterable (like itertools.starmap); Pool.starmap.__code__.co_argcount is 4 (same as map); Pool.starmap.__code__.co_varnames.__len__() is 4 (no extra locals, same as map); NEW in extra126: first standalone Pool.starmap qualname length invariant in mppoolvarnames126 namespace; wave 256; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: code_inspection
